'''Steven Barnes''' (born [[March 1]], [[1950s|1952]] in Los Angeles) is a science fiction writer, who wrote the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] novel ''[[The Cestus Deception]]'' and accompanying e-book ''[[The Hive]]''. He also wrote the book ''[[Mace Windu: The Glass Abyss]]''. He is married to author [[Wikipedia:Tananarive Due|Tananarive Due]], and the couple live in Los Angeles. Barnes has a daughter, Lauren Nicole, from his first marriage and a son, Jason, from his current marriage.

Barnes has had a varied education, including a secondary education at Los Angeles High School. He continued at Pepperdine University, majoring in Communication Arts. He is a certified hypnotherapist, trained at the Transformative Arts Institute in San Anselmo, California.

His true passion, other than writing, is [[Wikipedia:martial arts|martial and physical arts]]. He is a Black Belt in [[Wikipedia:Kenpo|Kenpo Karate]], and [[Wikipedia:Judo|Kodokan Judo]]. He holds an instructor certificate in [[Wikipedia:Wu Ming Ta|Wu Ming Ta]], and has an instructor candidate ranking in [[Wikipedia:Filipino Kali|Filipino Kali]] stick and knife fighting. He is an advanced student in [[Wikipedia:Jun Fan|Jun Fan]] Kickboxing, and is an instructor in [[Wikipedia:Wu Style Tai Chi Chuan|Wu Style Tai Chi Chuan]]. He is also an intermediate student in self defense pistol shooting.

He also holds a Brown Belt in [[Wikipedia:Jujutsu|Shorenji Jiu Jitsu]], and intermediate rankings in [[Wikipedia:Tae Kwon Do|Tae Kwon Do]] and [[Wikipedia:Aikido|Aikido]]. He has additional experience in boxing, Western fencing, wrestling, Wing Chun Kung Fu, Shotokan Karate, and French Savate.

He has completed the Yoga Works basic [[Wikipedia:Hatha Yoga|Hatha Yoga]] instructor program.

He is presently studying [[Wikipedia:Pentjak Silat|Pentjak Silat]] (an Indonesian fighting system) with Guru [[Wikipedia:Stevan Plinck|Stevan Plinck]], and [[Wikipedia:Ashtanga Vinyasa Yoga|Ashtanga Yoga]], an aerobic form of yoga.

